* LoadBalancer :
A Load Balancer is used to distribute incoming traffic across multiple servers or application instances so that 
no single server gets overloaded.
• Distributes user requests across multiple servers
• Improves application performance and response time
• Prevents server overload
• Provides high availability (if one server goes down, traffic goes to others)
• Helps in scaling applications easily
• Monitoring server health checks

Strategy Used By LoadBalancer :
  •  Round Robin – Sends requests one by one to each server in sequence.
  •  Least Connections – Sends traffic to the server with the fewest active connections.
  •  Weighted Round Robin – Distributes requests based on server capacity using assigned weights.
  •  IP Hash – Uses the client’s IP address to decide which server handles the request.
  •  Least Response Time – Sends requests to the server with the fastest response time.
  •  Random with Weight – Randomly selects a server, but higher-capacity servers get more traffic.
