🌍 Cluster Overview

We use a MongoDB replica set deployed across multiple regions to ensure high availability, disaster recovery, and read scalability.

South Europe → Primary (Writer)
North Europe → Secondary (Reader)
North America → Secondary (Reader)

Data Flow & Replication
All write operations are routed to the Primary node (South Europe)
The Primary records operations in the oplog (operation log)
Secondary nodes (North Europe & North America) continuously replicate data asynchronously from the oplog

Failover Mechanism
If the Primary node (South Europe) goes down:
An automatic election is triggered
One of the Secondary nodes becomes the new Primary
Application reconnects automatically via the MongoDB driver

Application microservices are deployed in Azure and connect to MongoDB using Private Endpoints
Microservice (Azure VNet) → Private Endpoint → MongoDB Cluster
